From 

P. lacihoveyensis

, the new species differs in having a longer body (vs L51.22– 
1.55 mm
); simple amphid (vs duplex); longer expanded part of pharynx (vs 
31–37 mm
); prerectum–intestine junction simple (vs prerectum–intestine junction guarded by three small cells); and longer spicules (vs 
27 mm
).
